{
  "texts": [
    "(A.4)Note that in contrast to (3.8), we do not impose any boundary condition at η 0 for ∆G (h).",
    "Upon symmetrizing over η 1 ↔ η 2, we are left with∆G (h) σ (η 1, η 2, k) = A h σ * h (η 1, k)σ * h (η 2, k).",
    "(A.5)Here A h = A h (κ, µ) is a helicity-dependent constant to be determined.",
    "Now we demand that this connected propagator is helically real after rotation, i.e.",
    "C(h)σ (χ 1, χ 2, k) * = C(-h) σ (χ 1, χ 2, k)."
  ]
}